Cinematch AI - System Manual
1. System Overview
Technology Stack
Frontend: React (Vite), Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion
Backend: Python Flask, Gunicorn
Machine Learning: Scikit-learn (SVM, TF-IDF), NLTK
Generative AI: Google Gemini API

2. Prerequisites & Requirements
Before installing the system, ensure your environment meets the following requirements:
Hardware Requirements
Operating System: Windows 10/11, macOS, or Linux.
RAM: Minimum 8GB recommended.
Disk Space: At least 2GB of free space.
Internet Connection: Required for API calls (Gemini) and package installation.

Software Requirements
Node.js: Version 16.0.0 or higher.
npm: Installed automatically with Node.js.
Python: Version 3.11 or higher.
Git: For version control (optional but recommended).

3. Backend Setup (Python/Flask)
The backend handles the machine learning model predictions and chatbot logic.

Step 3.1: Navigate to Backend Directory
Open your terminal and navigate to the backend folder:
cd BACKEND

Step 3.2: Virtual Environment (Optional but Recommended)
It is best practice to run the backend in an isolated environment.
# Windows
python -m venv venv
.\venv\Scripts\activate

# Mac/Linux
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
Step 3.3: Install Dependencies

--Install all required Python libraries using the requirements.txt file.
Required Libraries:

pandas
scikit-learn
nltk
joblib
google-generativeai
python-dotenv
flask
flask-cors
gunicorn

--Installation Command:
pip install -r requirements.txt

(Or install manually: pip install pandas scikit-learn nltk joblib google-generativeai python-dotenv flask flask-cors gunicorn)

Step 3.4: Configuration (.env)
--Create a file named .env inside the BACKEND folder. Add your Google Gemini API key:
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_actual_api_key_here
Step 3.5: Run the Server

--Start the Flask development server:
python api.py

You should see output indicating the server is running on http://127.0.0.1:5000.

4. Frontend Setup (React)

The frontend provides the user interface.
Step 4.1: Navigate to Frontend Directory
Open a new terminal window (keep the backend running) and navigate to the frontend folder:
cd NLP_PROJECT_FRONTEND

Step 4.2: Install Dependencies
Run the following commands to install React, Tailwind CSS, and utility libraries:
1. Core Dependencies:

npm install

# OR if installing manually based on requirements:
npm install react-router-dom lucide-react framer-motion clsx tailwind-merge

2. Development Dependencies (Typescript & Tailwind):

npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
npm install -D @types/react @types/react-dom

3. Initialize Tailwind Configuration:

npx tailwindcss init -p

Step 4.3: Start the Application

Run the development server:

npm run dev

You should see a local URL, typically http://localhost:5173. Open this in your browser.

5. Deployment Guide (Render)

If deploying to a production environment (like Render), follow these specific configurations.

Backend Deployment (Web Service)

Build Command: pip install -r requirements.txt

Start Command: gunicorn api:app

Environment Variables: Add GEMINI_API_KEY in the dashboard settings.

Frontend Deployment (Static Site)

Build Command: npm install; npm run build

Publish Directory: dist

Rewrites: Ensure a rewrite rule is added:

Source: /*

Destination: /index.html (To support React Router).

6. Directory Structure

Ensure your file structure looks like this for the system to function correctly:

PROJECT_ROOT/
├── .gitignore
├── BACKEND/
│   ├── .env                 # API Keys
│   ├── api.py               # Main Flask Application
│   ├── requirements.txt     # Python Dependencies
│   └── TF-IDF and SVM/      # Model Files
│       ├── movie_genre_multilabel_svm.pkl
│       ├── tfidf_vectorizer.pkl
│       └── genre_binarizer.pkl
│
└── NLP_PROJECT_FRONTEND/
    ├── package.json         # Node Dependencies
    ├── vite.config.js
    ├── index.html
    └── src/
        ├── main.tsx
        └── app/
            ├── App.tsx
            └── pages/       # React Pages
